workflow.name: Beginner data analysis: merge, filter & summarize in Google Sheets with GPT-4o
workflow.description:

parameters.content:
### üìå Merge Multiple Datasets

Pull two Google Sheets:

- **Marketing data** (performance metrics)  
- **Leader assignment** (who manages each channel)

Then merge the two sheets based on the **Channel** field.

---

### üìå Filter and If Steps

**Step 1:** Filter records with **Clicks ‚â• 5**  
**Step 2:** Branch logic:

- If **Spend ‚â• 350** ‚Üí `"Great"` outcome  
- Else ‚Üí `"Poor"` outcome

---

### üìå Summarize and Set Steps

For each branch (**Great** / **Poor**):

- Count the number of rows per **Leader**  
- Assign outcome labels  
- Prepare fields like `Leader`, `Outcome`, and `Day count`

---

### üìå Analyze Results with an AI Agent

- Merge both sets of labeled outcomes  
- Convert to a readable text format  
- Use an **AI Agent** to summarize and compare performance of leaders  
- Output a **paragraph** that identifies the **best** and **worst** performers and **why**

### üìå Setup Instructions

Before running the workflow:

1. **Copy the sample Google Sheet**  
   [Click here to copy the Google Sheet](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/19aUQYZq02qHsCelO4eeV4sx_MTJJupC5qe0gDLQBtRA/copy)

2. **Connect Google Sheets API**  
   - In n8n, go to **Credentials** and create a **Google Sheets OAuth2** credential.
   - Make sure to authorize access to the copied spreadsheet.

3. **Add your OpenAI API Key**  
   - In the **AI Agent** step, connect your **OpenAI credential** using your API key.

---

data.details:
The IF node can be used to implement binary conditional logic in your workflow. You can set up one-to-many conditions to evaluate each item of data being inputted into the node. That data will either evaluate to TRUE or FALSE and route out of the node accordingly.

This node has multiple types of conditions: Bool, String, Number, and Date & Time.

data.details: The Code node allows you to execute JavaScript in your workflow.

The Filter node can be used to filter items based on a condition. If the condition is met, the item will be passed on to the next node. If the condition is not met, the item will be omitted. Conditions can be combined together by AND(meet all conditions), or OR(meet at least one condition).
